# âš™ï¸ 5. `build.sh` (Dependency Bundling)

```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -e

rm -rf build/ package.zip
mkdir build
pip install -r requirements.txt -t build/
cp -r src/* build/
cd build
zip -r ../package.zip .
cd ..
echo "âœ… Zipped code+deps to package.zip"
```
- Mark as executable: `chmod +x build.sh`

---

# ğŸš€ 6. `deploy.sh` (Deployment Command)

```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -e

# Replace with your AWS Lambda function name
LAMBDA_NAME="your-lambda-function-name"

bash build.sh
aws lambda update-function-code \
    --function-name $LAMBDA_NAME \
    --zip-file fileb://package.zip

echo "âœ… Deployed to Lambda: $LAMBDA_NAME"
```
- Mark as executable: `chmod +x deploy.sh`

